<br>
When I was duoing sirens in CS with a mage friend, and had IC up, I managed to drop it on him for full damage, (which was very satisfying after all our Arena contests, BTW).  I suppose that taught him to shirk his CR, one shot kills are kinda fun, even if you aren't intending them.  <br>
<br>
As of the 'pre-Luclin, post 66% nerf' era when this happened, though, charmed players did not stick to the 66% damage rule with regular nukes.  I would be very surprised if the engine imposed the 75% of max hp rule on us while ignoring the 66%.  Sure, they could have altered the coding some to put these in, but that would require altering Mob AI instead of spell data, and we haven't heard anything about that change in any of the patch messages.  Anything that major would probably have warranted a heads up.<br>
